[DhtmlXQ_comment17]The main purpose of this move is to try to limit the movment of the black pieces on the cannon rank.||C8=9 would lead to stable formations for both sides,||Please click on the variations to understand why.[/DhtmlXQ_comment17]
[DhtmlXQ_comment18]This would be a more steadfast approach by black. R6+5 would probably allow red to be better![/DhtmlXQ_comment18]
[DhtmlXQ_comment22]And both sides are relatively equal.||In summary, when black chooses the left central cannon to counter the elephant opening, anything is possible. Red could use the screen horse formation, the sandwich horse formation...||In this example,as it is red who plays the screen horse defense, red is able to play one extra elephant move. This in an important difference to appreciate as Red would now start the game with a more defensive formation. Most of the time, the game would be a battle of formations and a test of patience. It would be easy to get into sticky situations for both sides and if black tries to attack too aggressively, black would be vulnerable to forceful and rapid counters from red.[/DhtmlXQ_comment22]
